    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\n```\nError detected while processing TermRequest Autocommands for \"*\":\nError executing lua callback: vim/_defaults.lua:0: Invalid 'line': out of range\nstack traceback:\n\t[C]: in function 'nvim_buf_set_extmark'\n\tvim/_defaults.lua: in function <vim/_defaults.lua:0>\n```\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```lua\n-- term.lua\nvim.cmd([[\n  term sh -c \"printf '\\n\\n\\e]133;A\\e\\\\'; sh\"\n]])\nvim.cmd(\"set modifiable\")\nvim.api.nvim_feedkeys(\"dG]]\", 'm', false)\n```\n\nRun `nvim --clean -S term.lua`\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nI don't expect a nvim error that steals focus from a TermRequest callback, since this could trigger from terminal output. The repro triggers this through `]]`, but I've see the same error by running commands in `fish` after editing the terminal buffer.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.11.4\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nLinux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\n1.2.0\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-ghostty\n\n### Installation\n\nArch",
