        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> Error detected while processing TermRequest Autocommands for \"*\":\n> Error executing lua callback: vim/_defaults.lua:0: Invalid 'line': out of range\n> stack traceback:\n> \t[C]: in function 'nvim_buf_set_extmark'\n\nEven if this error is ignored, then when `]]` is next used, `nvim_win_set_cursor` will raise error:\n\n```\nE5108: Lua: .../runtime//lua/vim/_defaults.lua:618: Cursor position outside buffer\nstack traceback:\n\t[C]: in function 'nvim_win_set_cursor'\n\t.../runtime//lua/vim/_defaults.lua:618: in function 'jump_to_prompt'\n```\n\n# Analysis\n\nThis is because the extmarks aren't adjusted after deleting lines (which may happen if 'scrollback' is exceeded, or by setting 'modifiable' as described above).\n\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/c94b7b93c0d9f843be6b68db9dee0a0297060af4/runtime/lua/vim/_defaults.lua#L616-L618\n\n# Proposal\n\nI think extmarks are supposed to handle this automatically, maybe this is just a missing feature in `terminal.c`? ",
