            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Maybe off topic, but extmarks not being automatically adjusted in term buffers might also be the cause of a related bug with `[[`.\n\nAt a shell prompt in the middle of the buffer, `cat` a file big enough to have the prompt discarded due to exceeding scrollback limit. Then `[[` ends up in the middle of the `cat` output. Jumping to the top of the buffer feels less wrong for this situation.",
