            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> This is because the extmarks aren't adjusted after deleting lines (which may happen if 'scrollback' is exceeded, or by setting 'modifiable' as described above).\n\nI don't think this is related to the error. I think the cause of this error (the one in `nvim_win_set_cursor`, not `nvim_buf_set_extmark`) is that the extmarks used for OSC 133 have right gravity, so they move one line beyond the end of the buffer when all lines are deleted. With left gravity this doesn't seems to happen:\n```diff\ndiff --git a/runtime/lua/vim/_defaults.lua b/runtime/lua/vim/_defaults.lua\nindex f728bb9949..b898c97d3e 100644\n--- a/runtime/lua/vim/_defaults.lua\n+++ b/runtime/lua/vim/_defaults.lua\n@@ -580,7 +580,13 @@ do\n     callback = function(args)\n       if string.match(args.data.sequence, '^\\027]133;A') then\n         local lnum = args.data.cursor[1] ---@type integer\n-        vim.api.nvim_buf_set_extmark(args.buf, nvim_terminal_prompt_ns, lnum - 1, 0, {})\n+        vim.api.nvim_buf_set_extmark(\n+          args.buf,\n+          nvim_terminal_prompt_ns,\n+          lnum - 1,\n+          0,\n+          { right_gravity = false }\n+        )\n       end\n     end,\n   })\n```",
